Tom,<br><br>
I posted earlier in a string long since forgotten about seeing ships in Haiphong harbor flying Nato country flags.  Canada and others as well as Russian.  There were instructions to ensure that bombing did not accidently hit one of the allied ships.<br><br>
Commerce continued.  All type of supplies found ther way through this port.  Is it any wonder we received ordinance from a NATO source.  This war was strange.  Anyone not directly involved in the conflict seemed to be reaping the rewards from market opportunity.<br><br>
I was never sure about the depth of the problem just positive it was happening.
